Description: The rest on the flight into Egypt, the Holy Family are in the centre being offered fruit by John the Baptist at right, a large angel collects from the fruit from the tree and above three putti hover in a cloud, after Titian. 1569 Engraving
Associated names: Representation of: St John the Baptist (Prodromos)
Acquisition notes: The 208 items in the 1950 purchase from the Liechtenstein collection consisted of Italian prints. They were views of Rome; prints after Titian; portraits of Roman Emperors; and various other prints after Venetian artists.
